    <h2>Common Budget Pouch Questions</h2>

    <h3>Do cheap nicotine pouches have the same nicotine strength as premium brands?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Nicotine strength is regulated and independently tested. A 13mg KUMA pouch contains the same amount of nicotine as a 13mg ZYN. Strength labelling is consistent across price tiers. The difference lies in flavour intensity, pouch texture, and packaging — not core formulation.</p>

    <h3>Why is AVANT Cool Mint so cheap?</h3>
    <p>AVANT is a direct-to-consumer brand with minimal marketing overhead. They pass savings to customers. Minimal packaging, streamlined distribution, and no celebrity endorsements keep costs low without sacrificing quality. It's genuinely good value, not a loss-leader.</p>

    <h3>Will budget pouches damage my gums?</h3>
    <p>No. All nicotine pouches — budget or premium — carry similar gum health considerations. Damage depends on usage duration and placement, not brand or price. Budget pouches meet the same safety standards as premium alternatives. If you experience gum irritation, rotate placement and reduce session length.</p>

    <h3>Are KUMA pouches less popular because they're cheap?</h3>
    <p>KUMA has a small but loyal following. They're less well-known due to lower marketing spend, not inferior quality. In fact, informed users deliberately choose KUMA over premium brands. You're not settling — you're being smart.</p>

    <h3>What's the shelf life of budget nicotine pouches?</h3>
    <p>All nicotine pouches — regardless of price — remain stable for 12–18 months if stored in a cool, dry place. Budget brands have identical shelf life to premium ones. We rotate stock regularly, so everything you order is fresh.</p>

